HYBOSA. Hybosa‚ Boheman, Monogr. Cassid. iii. p. 1 (1855).

Eight species of this Tropical-American genus have been described, one only of which enters our region. Hybosa is chiefly distinguished by the base of the prothorax being strongly bisinuate on either side, with a broadly produced obtuse median lobe.
